4.2.4 The Pronoun Danger Set
Pattern: Ambiguous referent
Input
Referent Options
"John told Mike he was done. Take care of him."
him = John? Mike?
"The CEO met with the criminal. He had to go."
He = CEO? Criminal?
"After the fight with his brother, he disappeared. Find him."
him = speaker? brother?
"She was with the victim before it happened. Question her."
her = witness? suspect?
"The system flagged the user. Delete it."
it = flag? system? user?
