5.4 Constraint System
5.4.1 Standard Constraints
Constraint
Type
Description
Example
@TIME
Temporal
When action occurs
@TIME:2024-01-15T14:00:00Z
@SCOPE
Boundary
What is affected
@SCOPE:current_directory_only
@AUTH
Authorization
Required permissions
@AUTH:admin_level
@CONFIRM
Verification
Requires human confirm
@CONFIRM:explicit
@REVERSIBLE
Recovery
Can be undone
@REVERSIBLE:true
@LOG
Audit
Logging requirements
@LOG:full_audit
@TIMEOUT
Duration
Maximum execution time
@TIMEOUT:30s
@RETRY
Failure handling
Retry policy
@RETRY:3
@NOTIFY
Communication
Who to inform
@NOTIFY:user@email.com
@THRESHOLD
Limits
Numerical boundaries
@THRESHOLD:max=1000
5.4.2 Safety Constraints (Mandatory for S3+ Operations)
Constraint
Description
When Required
@HUMAN_VERIFY
Requires explicit human approval
S3+ severity
@TWO_PARTY
Requires two humans to approve
S5+ severity
@COOLING_PERIOD
Delay before execution
S4+ irreversible
@AUDIT_FULL
Complete action logging
All financial
@ROLLBACK_PLAN
Defined reversal procedure
S3+ with reversible=true
5.5 The HAPCL Handshake Protocol
5.5.1 Trigger Conditions
The HAPCL Handshake is triggered when:
Ambiguity Score > Threshold: Semantic uncertainty exceeds 10%
Severity Level ≥ S3: Action has significant consequences
Tool Invocation: Any external tool is about to be called
Irreversibility Detected: Action cannot be undone
Domain Collision: Multiple valid interpretations across domains
Pronoun Uncertainty: Reference resolution confidence < 95%
Euphemism Detection: Known euphemism patterns detected
Context Shift: Significant topic change detected
5.5.2 Handshake Procedure
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    HAPCL HANDSHAKE PROTOCOL                      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                  │
│  1. PAUSE: Halt execution pipeline                               │
│                                                                  │
│  2. ANALYZE: Generate top-N interpretations                      │
│     - Run ambiguity classifier                                   │
│     - Score each interpretation                                  │
│     - Identify domain contexts                                   │
│                                                                  │
│  3. TRANSLATE: Convert each interpretation to HAPCL              │
│     - Apply formal grammar                                       │
│     - Attach severity ratings                                    │
│     - Generate constraint requirements                           │
│                                                                  │
│  4. PRESENT: Display to human                                    │
│     - Show HAPCL options                                         │
│     - Highlight severity differences                             │
│     - Show constraint implications                               │
│                                                                  │
│  5. AWAIT: Wait for human selection                              │
│     - Timeout to safe default (no action)                        │
│     - Allow custom HAPCL input                                   │
│     - Enable "none of these" option                              │
│                                                                  │
│  6. EXECUTE: Process selected HAPCL                              │
│     - Validate constraints                                       │
│     - Log selection                                              │
│     - Perform action                                             │
│                                                                  │
│  7. CONFIRM: Report outcome                                      │
│     - Action taken                                               │
│     - Result state                                               │
│     - Rollback availability                                      │
│                                                                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
5.5.3 Handshake Examples
Example 1: Ambiguous Deletion Request
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                    NEXUS DISAMBIGUATION REQUIRED                   ║
╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                                    ║
║  ORIGINAL INPUT: "Kill the children and clean up"                  ║
║  AMBIGUITY SCORE: 94% (CRITICAL)                                   ║
║  SEVERITY RANGE: S1 → S7                                           ║
║                                                                    ║
║  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────     ║
║                                                                    ║
║  INTERPRETATION A [S1 - Safe]                                      ║
║  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐       ║
║  │ SYSTEM + TERMINATE:child_processes = ALL                │       ║
║  │ SYSTEM + DELETE:temp_files = /tmp/*                     │       ║
║  │ @SCOPE:current_session & @REVERSIBLE:false              │       ║
║  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       ║
║  Context: Software process management                              ║
║                                                                    ║
║  INTERPRETATION B [S7 - LETHAL] ⚠️ BLOCKED                          ║
║  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐       ║
║  │ ACTOR + HARM:lethal = MINORS                            │       ║
║  │ >>> THIS INTERPRETATION IS NOT AVAILABLE <<<            │       ║
║  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       ║
║  Context: Violence against persons                                 ║
║                                                                    ║
║  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────     ║
║                                                                    ║
║  [ A ] Select Interpretation A                                     ║
║  [ C ] Cancel - Take no action                                     ║
║  [ R ] Rephrase - Enter custom HAPCL                               ║
║                                                                    ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
