9.2 Proposed Research Directions
9.2.1 Semantic Fingerprinting
Develop unique "fingerprints" for meaning that are robust to paraphrase but sensitive to semantic shift.
Hypothesis: A robust semantic representation should:
Be invariant to syntactic variation
Be variant to meaning change
Enable precise similarity measurement
Support cross-lingual comparison
9.2.2 Pragmatic Pretraining
Create training datasets and objectives specifically for pragmatic understanding.
Proposed Approach:
Collect ambiguous instruction datasets with ground truth intentions
Train models to predict full HAPCL from ambiguous natural language
Evaluate on held-out pragmatic test sets
9.2.3 Formal Verification for HAPCL
Apply formal methods to prove properties of HAPCL execution.
Goals:
Prove that valid HAPCL cannot express certain harmful actions
Verify that the translation from NL → HAPCL preserves intent
Establish bounds on interpretation error
9.2.4 Adversarial Ambiguity Generation
Red-team by automatically generating maximally ambiguous attacks.
Approach:
Train generator to produce ambiguous statements
Reward for: (a) passing initial filters, (b) triggering wrong interpretation
Use generated examples to harden the Nexus Interceptor
