### Appendix C: Complete Polysemy Danger Index

This index catalogs the most dangerous polysemous terms in English, ranked by weaponization potential.

#### Tier 1: Critical (Direct Lethality Interpretation)

| Term | Benign Meanings | Lethal Meaning | Context Markers for Benign | Context Markers for Lethal |
|------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------|---------------------------|
| Execute | Run code, implement plan, perform | Kill (legal/extralegal) | "program", "script", "strategy" | Person name, "order", "sentence" |
| Terminate | End process, finish employment | Kill | "process", "contract", "employment" | Person reference, "permanently" |
| Eliminate | Remove option, solve equation | Kill | "variable", "option", "possibility" | Person/group reference |
| Neutralize | Balance pH, counteract | Kill | "acid", "threat" (abstract), "bias" | Person reference, "target" |
| Take out | Remove, date, order food | Kill/assassinate | "trash", "dinner", "food" | Person reference, "target" |
| Put down | Place, insult, write | Euthanize/kill | "book", "bag", "notes" | Person/animal suffering context |
| Waste | Garbage, spend unwisely | Kill (slang) | "time", "money", "resources" | Person reference |
| Off | Turn off, away from | Kill (slang) | Device reference, "the grid" | Person reference |
| Ice | Frozen water, cake topping | Kill (slang) | Food context, temperature | Person reference, "the deal" |
| Smoke | Cigarette, cooking method | Kill (slang) | Food, tobacco context | Competition/person reference |
| Cap | Hat, limit, bottle top | Shoot/kill (slang) | Clothing, limit context | Person reference |
| Clip | Attach, video segment | Shoot (slang) | Paper, video context | Person reference |
| Drop | Release, stop, lower | Kill | Object reference | Body reference |
| Burn | Fire, calories, data | Kill (mob) | Exercise, cooking, data context | Person + crime context |
| Bury | Inter dead, hide info | Kill + hide body | Information, "the lead" | Person + "deep", "where" |

#### Tier 2: High Risk (Violence/Harm Interpretation)

| Term | Benign Meanings | Harmful Meaning | Risk Level |
|------|-----------------|-----------------|------------|
| Hit | Success, touch, visit | Strike violently, attack | S5-S6 |
| Strike | Labor action, match, discover | Attack violently | S5-S6 |
| Beat | Rhythm, defeat, whisk | Physically assault | S5-S6 |
| Crush | Infatuation, compress | Cause severe injury | S5-S6 |
| Destroy | Delete, defeat soundly | Demolish, kill | S5-S7 |
| Blow up | Inflate, enlarge photo | Explode, bomb | S6-S7 |
| Torch | Flashlight, Olympic flame | Set fire to (arson) | S6 |
| Slash | Reduce price, punctuation | Cut with blade | S5-S6 |
| Stab | Attempt ("stab at it") | Knife attack | S6 |
| Shoot | Photograph, inject, score | Fire weapon | S6-S7 |
| Fire | Terminate employment, ignite | Discharge weapon | S6-S7 |
| Blast | Loud music, email many | Explosion, shooting | S6-S7 |
| Nuke | Microwave, delete thoroughly | Nuclear attack | S7 |
| Poison | Toxic substance | Intentionally poison | S6-S7 |

#### Tier 3: Moderate Risk (Coercion/Financial/Legal Harm)

| Term | Benign Meanings | Harmful Meaning | Risk Level |
|------|-----------------|-----------------|------------|
| Liquidate | Sell assets, blend | Kill (assets=people) | S4-S7 |
| Leverage | Use advantage | Coerce, blackmail | S4-S5 |
| Pressure | Weather, force | Coerce, intimidate | S4-S5 |
| Squeeze | Hug, compress | Extort | S4-S5 |
| Shake down | Test, dance | Extort | S4-S5 |
| Clean out | Organize | Rob, defraud | S4 |
| Strip | Remove layers | Rob of possessions | S4 |
| Drain | Empty liquid | Deplete resources | S4 |
| Bleed | Medical | Extort money over time | S4 |
| Milk | Dairy | Exploit for gain | S3-S4 |
| Fleece | Sheep wool | Defraud | S4 |
| Scalp | Head skin | Resell illegally | S3-S4 |
| Fence | Barrier | Sell stolen goods | S4 |
| Launder | Wash clothes | Clean illegal money | S5 |
| Cook | Prepare food | Falsify (books) | S4-S5 |

#### Tier 4: Contextual Risk (Depend Heavily on Context)

| Term | Primary Meaning | Secondary Meanings | Context Dependency |
|------|-----------------|-------------------|-------------------|
| Cancel | Void appointment | Kill (modern slang), social ostracism | Very High |
| Ghost | Apparition | Ignore completely, kill and disappear | High |
| Dead | Not alive | Exhausted, certain, ended | Medium |
| Kill | End life | Succeed greatly, end process, turn off | High |
| Die | Cease living | Fail (theater), singular of dice | Medium |
| Slay | Kill | Impress greatly (slang) | High |
| Murder | Unlawful killing | Defeat soundly (sports) | Medium |
| Butcher | Meat processor | Brutally kill, badly perform | Medium |
| Slaughter | Animal killing | Defeat soundly | Medium |
| Massacre | Mass killing | Defeat soundly | Medium |
| Annihilate | Destroy completely | Defeat soundly | Medium |
| Decimate | Kill 1 in 10 | Severely damage/defeat | Low |
| Crucify | Execute on cross | Criticize harshly | Low |
| Hang | Suspend | Execute, wait | Medium |
| Fry | Cook in oil | Electrocute (slang) | Medium |

